It runs as XML over HTTP,
so you can monitor and configure

00:12:44.700 --> 00:12:46.280
your services remotely.

00:12:46.280 --> 00:12:50.480
You can configure and monitor
multiple services from within the app.

00:12:50.480 --> 00:12:54.840
And one cool feature we've added in
Panther Server is the ability to easily

00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:57.680
replicate configurations between servers.

00:12:57.760 --> 00:12:59.960
So for instance,
if you have a server configuration,

00:12:59.960 --> 00:13:02.600
like a file server or a web server,
and you've set it up,

00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:05.280
and you want to replicate
that across a bank of servers,

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:08.860
you can now just take that configuration
and drag it from one service to another,

00:13:08.860 --> 00:13:11.260
and it will automatically
configure the second server,

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:12.460
or the third, or the fourth.

00:13:12.460 --> 00:13:17.370
So it makes it very easy in a single
step to configure multiple servers and

00:13:17.370 --> 00:13:20.990
to change your configurations across
multiple servers on an ongoing basis.

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:23.100
Again, very simple,
a very cool feature that's

00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:24.940
new in Panther Server.

