So next is web services.

00:39:09.680 --> 00:39:11.660
In Panther Server,
we're once again including

00:39:11.660 --> 00:39:12.680
the Apache web server.

00:39:12.680 --> 00:39:17.320
We have performance-optimized
Apache web server.

00:39:17.320 --> 00:39:22.100
We're able to do far more
connections than a typical Apache web

00:39:22.100 --> 00:39:23.320
server would be able to do.

00:39:23.340 --> 00:39:25.620
It's even a little faster in Panther.

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:30.710
We ship 1.3 as the default web server,
and that's actually the one

00:39:30.750 --> 00:39:33.420
that you'd be configuring when
you're in the server admin.

00:39:33.420 --> 00:39:36.070
But we do include 2.0,
so people who do want to use that,

00:39:36.070 --> 00:39:36.630
it's there.

00:39:36.670 --> 00:39:37.400
You can use it.

00:39:37.480 --> 00:39:43.660
Part of the problem we've seen is that
