00:41:34.650 --> 00:41:39.500
So in Mac OS X Server,
we are leveraging the best standards

00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:43.040
and the best technologies to bring
you the best application servers.

00:41:45.080 --> 00:41:47.960
But first, there is Java.

00:41:48.040 --> 00:41:52.320
Java has evolved as an
OS on top of the OS.

00:41:52.350 --> 00:41:58.700
Nowadays, application servers are huge,
multi-threaded beasts.

00:41:58.740 --> 00:42:00.290
They are all implemented in Java.

00:42:00.400 --> 00:42:03.600
They spawn thousands of
simultaneous threads.

00:42:03.650 --> 00:42:07.320
They open and close
thousands of I/O connections.

00:42:07.370 --> 00:42:12.580
And they necessitate an enterprise-grade
Java VM underneath them.

00:42:12.820 --> 00:42:18.460
That's what we are providing with a
JDK 1.4 and a JDK 1.3 implementation.

00:42:22.980 --> 00:42:26.740
Now the big news today is JBoss.

00:42:26.800 --> 00:42:29.210
JBoss is very popular out there.

00:42:29.220 --> 00:42:31.550
It is popular for three reasons.

00:42:31.580 --> 00:42:35.120
It's free, it's free, and it's free.

00:42:38.900 --> 00:42:45.000
How do you bundle free software
and do not show up as a freeloader?

00:42:45.080 --> 00:42:46.170
You add value.

00:42:46.320 --> 00:42:50.380
And we believe we are adding
tremendous value on top of JBoss.

00:42:51.450 --> 00:42:54.550
The real three reasons for
JBoss being popular are its

00:42:54.550 --> 00:42:57.280
unbeatable quality for the price,

00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:01.720
I'm going to improve.

00:43:01.740 --> 00:43:05.640
The next one is its
perceived ease of use.

00:43:05.640 --> 00:43:09.080
And the third one is its modular design.

00:43:11.570 --> 00:43:18.330
It is perceived ease of use,
but as Marc Fleury, the JBoss founder,

00:43:18.330 --> 00:43:23.550
says, they are pushing the envelope
at the container level,

00:43:23.550 --> 00:43:29.800
which means that they are not really
investing in the deployment ease of use.

00:43:29.820 --> 00:43:34.150
Developers love JBoss.

00:43:34.150 --> 00:43:34.150
Deployers hate it.

00:43:34.370 --> 00:43:40.180
If you're a sysadmin, to use JBoss,
you'll have to speak XML in your dreams.

00:43:43.120 --> 00:43:46.910
Now,
this is going to be a dream come true.

00:43:47.000 --> 00:43:54.260
We are introducing tools to enable you to
deploy JBoss easily on Mac OS X Server.

00:43:54.950 --> 00:43:58.240
Our goal is to make
Mac OS X Server the best platform

00:43:58.240 --> 00:44:01.510
to deploy J2EE applications.

00:44:02.650 --> 00:44:04.320
We are doing this in three steps.

00:44:04.350 --> 00:44:08.610
First, JBoss is integrated in
the server admin plugin.

00:44:09.230 --> 00:44:12.280
Second,
there is a JBoss deployment tool that

00:44:12.350 --> 00:44:16.650
lets you take J2E applications from

00:44:16.910 --> 00:44:22.670
IDEs and package them,
talking to the JBoss server,

00:44:22.960 --> 00:44:25.200
prepackage them to deploy them.

00:44:25.220 --> 00:44:29.020
And third,
there is a JBoss management console

00:44:29.040 --> 00:44:32.560
that lets you manage the JBoss server,
start and stop services,

00:44:32.560 --> 00:44:39.390
look at its statistics, and so on,
and manage the lifecycle

00:44:39.390 --> 00:44:39.390
of your applications.

00:44:40.450 --> 00:44:44.770
Now, this is all nice,
but where is the modular design?

00:44:44.790 --> 00:44:50.210
I'm going to give you a few examples of
services that we are bundling with JBoss.

00:44:50.720 --> 00:44:52.240
The first one is Tomcat.

00:44:52.240 --> 00:44:53.950
So you're all familiar with Tomcat.

00:44:54.040 --> 00:44:55.750
We've been shipping it for a while.

00:44:55.830 --> 00:45:00.370
We're revving the version to 4.1.x
because it's always evolving.

00:45:00.370 --> 00:45:03.090
And we integrated it in JBoss.

00:45:03.230 --> 00:45:09.700
So now Tomcat lives inside JBoss and
can be managed by the same tools that

00:45:09.770 --> 00:45:12.200
I talked about in the previous slides.

00:45:12.200 --> 00:45:17.220
And the servlet on GSP applications can
be prepackaged by the deployment tool.

00:45:20.210 --> 00:45:22.810
The WebObjects application server.

00:45:22.900 --> 00:45:29.110
WebObjects has been improved and will
be shipped as version 5.2.2 with a

00:45:29.110 --> 00:45:33.620
